rise_time

public java.util.Date rise_time
The date and time the user awoke. This is computed as "the time of day at the end of the last 5 minute block of sleep in the sleep graph." If no sleep is present in the sleep graph, the value is null

sleep_onset

public java.util.Date sleep_onset

alarm_reason

public int alarm_reason
Indicates the reason for the most recent alarm ringing. - 0 - REM to NREM Transition - 1 - NREM to REM Transition - 2 - Wake while awake - 3 - Prevent waking from Deep sleep - 4 - End of Wake Window - 5 - No Alarm

alarm_type

public int alarm_type
Indicates which alarm type is enabled. - 0 - standard wake - 1 - SmartWake

morning_feel

public int morning_feel
Indicates the user's perception of how they slept that night. Null indicates they entered no rating. - 1 - Terribly - 2 - Poorly - 3 - Okay - 4 - Well - 5 - Great

sleep_graph_5min

public int[] sleep_graph_5min
A 5-minute sleep graph containing a space-separated list of numbers. Each number represents a 5-minute time period (ex. a 6-hour sleep graph would have 72 integers). The sleep stages are encoded as: - 0 - undefined - 1 - Wake - 2 - REM - 3 - Light - 4 - Deep

sleep_graph_30sec

public int[] sleep_graph_30sec
A 30-second sleep graph containing a spaceseparated list of numbers. Each number represents a 30-second time period The sleep stages are encoded as: - 0 - undefined - 1 - wake - 2 - REM - 3 - Light - 4 - Deep
